            <p>Apiarist Donath lived at Spring Mill, thirteen miles north of Philadelphia.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <odd id="ref5">
            <head>Early American History Note</head>
            <p>Joseph Donath is believed to be the author of this journal. Donath was a Philadelphia merchant and retailer who was also an apiarist in Spring Mill, Pennsylvania, about thirteen miles north of Philadelphia, in the 1780s. This manuscript volume contains an account of Joseph Donath’s beehives from March 1787 to November 1788. The volume includes details on weather, bee behavior, and hive design, including sketches of his bee farm. Of note, Donath also records a visit on July 22, 1787 from George Washington, Thomas Mifflin, and four other members of the Constitutional Convention. The delegation asked Donath a number of questions and gave his efforts “their highest approbation.”</p>
        </odd>
